### 19. HOW THIS BOOK CAME TO BE FOUND

And Dĕmâtĕyôs (Domitius), the Archbishop of Rôm (*i.e.*, Constantinople,
Byzantium), said, "I have found in the Church of \[Saint\] Sophia among
the books and the royal treasures a manuscript \[which stated\] that the
whole kingdom of the world \[belonged\] to the Emperor of Rôm and the
Emperor of Ethiopia."

